HEADWORD: Mahabharatam
<hw>Ma*ha*bha"ra*tam</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Skr. <ets>mah⟦amac⟧bh⟦amac⟧rata</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Hinduism)</fld> <def>A celebrated sacred epic poem of the Hindus,
written in Sanskrit. It is of great length, and is chiefly devoted to a
history, in many episodes, of a civil war between two dynasties of
ancient India.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Mahabharatam, Mahabharatum.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

